      <akn:section eId="sec_4_205_47">
        <akn:num>4-205.47</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Nursing care standard.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_4-205_47_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>When a recipient is receiving nursing care in the home of a relative, the Mayor will apply the standard for room, board, and care in an intermediate care facility, based on the kind and extent of care required.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_4-205_47_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The rate for care in a foster home or for residential placement shall be the same as that for the lowest rate in an intermediate care facility.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_4-205_47_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The rates paid for intermediate care, foster home care, or residential placement shall be paid at 100% of the standard as the rates were not increased in the 1970 budget.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
